Task 3: Cloud-Based Bus Pass System 
Project Title
Cloud-Based Bus Pass Booking and Management System
1. Introduction
The Cloud-Based Bus Pass System is an online application that allows passengers to book bus passes, make payments, and download their passes through a cloud-hosted platform.
Traditional bus pass systems require users to visit transport offices physically, resulting in long queues and manual record management. This project automates the entire process and stores data securely in the cloud.
2. Objective
The objectives of this project are:
Provide online bus pass booking.
Reduce manual paperwork.
Manage passenger records efficiently.
Enable cloud-based access.
Improve scalability and reliability.
Generate digital bus passes.
3. Problem Statement
Traditional bus pass systems face several issues:
Long waiting times.
Manual data entry errors.
Difficult record management.
Limited accessibility.
High maintenance costs.
This system solves these issues using cloud computing technology.
